  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="letter">
        <head>
          <title>9 December 1746. – Exercise letter in Latin [by <persName key="p0829" ref="https://uri.gbv.de/terminology/lod_persons/b51ad807-64e4-4503-ba04-7e61f8c3bb5b">Prince Aleksandr Sergeevich Dolgorukov]</persName>
          </title>
          <note>
            <bibl>AVPRI, fond 2 VKD, opis 6, no. 1676, f. 7. Latin original.</bibl>
          </note>
        </head>
        
        <pb n="f. 7" />
        
        <p>Litterae extemporales</p>
        <p>
          <placeName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="g0019" xml:space="default" ref="https://www.geonames.org/2968815">Lutetia Parisiorum</placeName> nuper redux, Amice carissime, <placeName key="g0002" ref="https://www.geonames.org/498817">Petropolim</placeName> perveni. Amicitiae nostrae contrarium crederem,
          diuturnius; inde te in primis de adventu meo cetiorem facio. Utinam omnibus curis ac
          sollicitudinibus liber tuos lares petere atque tecum pristinam amicitiam fovere possem. Id
          cum vitae meae rationes non permittant, litterae amoris, quo te prosequor testes erunt. De
          meis <placeName cert="high" evidence="internal" full="yes" generatedBy="human" instant="unknown" key="g0019" xml:space="default" ref="https://www.geonames.org/2968815">Lutetia Parisiorum</placeName> occupationibus singula exponere
          non audeo, ne diuturno nimis tempore te mea epistola detineam. Quare nihil aliud
          perscribendum puto, nisi me, quantum liciut, tum oblectationibus, tum eriditorum
          frequentationi, opus dedisse. Iter, Deo duce, jucunde feliciterque perigi. Quae mihi
          postea evenient, ad te scribere non omittam. De valetudine tua, quaeso, me certiorem
          facias, meque tibi semper esse deditissimum certo certius credas.</p>
        <closer>
          <salute>In <orgName key="o0006" ref="https://uri.gbv.de/terminology/lod_organisations/171110b7-5487-4f01-a8b9-28103f4f2159">Academia Equestri Petropolitana</orgName> die 9.
            Dec[embri] 1746.</salute>
          <signed>
            <persName key="p0829" ref="https://uri.gbv.de/terminology/lod_persons/b51ad807-64e4-4503-ba04-7e61f8c3bb5b">Pr. Alexander Dolgoruky</persName>
          </signed>
        </closer>
